{
  "message": "test(corpus): add false-positive test fixtures for rule validation\n\nNew corpus fixtures demonstrating false-positive scenarios where rule\nanchors incorrectly fire on unrelated text:\n\nclaude_code/:\n- banner.txt/expect.json: Claude Code version banner detection\n- banner_near_miss.txt/expect.json: Similar text that shouldn't match\n- overloaded_fp_database.txt/expect.json: \"Database overloaded\" should\n  not trigger claude_code.error.overloaded rule (different context)\n- thinking_near_miss_v2.txt/expect.json: Generic \"Thinking\" word in\n  non-Claude contexts\n- timeout_error_fp_test_suite.txt/expect.json: \"Test suite timed out\"\n  should not trigger claude_code.error.timeout rule\n\nwezterm/:\n- connection_lost_fp_ssh.txt/expect.json: \"SSH connection lost\" should\n  not trigger wezterm.mux.connection_lost rule\n- pane_exited_near_miss.txt/expect.json: Similar exit text in wrong context\n\nThese fixtures enable automated regression testing for false-positive\nprevention and help identify rules with overly broad anchors that need\nadditional context requirements (e.g., preceding banner, agent type filter).\n\nSee docs/agent-quirks-catalog.md for mitigation strategies.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
